label.value: increased intron retention

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which introns are retained at some, but not all introns at a higher level with increased frequency. Weak donor sequences are more affected.

label.value: sensitive to amiloride

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to amiloride. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of amiloride that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: increased cell population growth on sorbitol carbon source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cell growth is increased relative to normal in a medium containing sorbitol as the carbon source.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: decreased phosphoglycerate mutase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a phosphoglycerate mutase activity is decreased.

label.value: abnormal de novo SAGA complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which de novo assembly of the SAGA complex is abnormal.

definition.value: Note that this term refers to the abnormal biogenesis of the complex, i.e. the process of building the complex from individual subunits. For assays identifyion alterations in complex subunit composition use 'abnormal protein complex composition FYPO:0005003' or  'abnormal protein-protein interaction" (FYPO:0000704) or their descendants.

label.value: decreased splicing of introns with branch point-distant 3â€™-splice site

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mRNA splicing via the spliceosome is decreased for specific introns with longer than average (>21 bp) branch site to acceptor distance.

label.value: normal morphology during phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype characterized by normal cell morphology (i.e. size, shape, and structure indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to phophate starvation.

label.value: decreased protein level in SAGA complex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a protein measured in the SAGA complex is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased protein level in NuA4 complex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a protein measured in the NuA4 complex is lower than normal.

label.value: increased mitochondrial fusion

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitochondrion fusion is increased.

label.value: loss  of viability in stationary phase upon phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable after entering stationary phase, when cells the population are subject to phosphate starvation.

label.value: increased nuclear envelope SPB fenestra size

value.value: A abnormal nuclear envelope organization phenotype in which SPB fenestra in the nuclear envelope are larger than normal. SPB fenestra are the result of SPB extrusion.

label.value: increased duration of nuclear envelope SPB fenestra

value.value: A abnormal nuclear envelope organization phenotype in which SPB fenestra in the nuclear envelope are present for longer than normal.

label.value: cytoplasmic protein mislocalized to nucleoplasm during mitotic M-phase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein that is normally found only in the cytoplasm  is observed in the nucleoplasm during mitotic M-phase.

label.value: ribosome mislocalized to nucleoplasm

value.value: A cell phenotype where a ribosome is mislocalized to the nucleoplasm in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: decreased vegetative cell population growth on low glucose

value.value: A vegetative cell population phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing low glucose. This term refers to situations where glucose is below 0.2%.

label.value: increased tRNA guanosine N2,N2-dimethylation

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the posttranscriptional addition of two methyl groups to the N2 position of a guanine residue in a tRNA molecule is increased. Normally, two methyl groups are transferred to the G26 residue.

label.value: increased stop codon readthrough

definition.value: A metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which translational readthough of a stop codon increases during cytoplasmic translation.

label.value: normal growth site selection after cell division

value.value: A phenotype in which the selection of the new growth site is at the old cell end .

label.value: increased calcium signaling

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which calcium signaling is increased.

label.value: decreased phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate level in the Golgi

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate measured in a cell is lower than normal in the Golgi.

label.value: normal cellular polyphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of polyphosphate measured in the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased protein localization tomitotic spindle pole body during G1/S

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is decreased during G1/S ofinterphase.

label.value: normal stop codon readthrough

value.value: A metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which translational readthough of a stop codon is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild-type) during cytoplasmic translation.

label.value: decreased size and number of lipid droplets

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which lipid droplets are smaller and more numerous than normal.

label.value: normal nucleocytoplasmic transport

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleocytoplasmic tranport is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Nucleocytoplasmic transportport is the directed movement of any substance into  or out of the nucleus; import or export of all substances or a specific substance may be affected.

label.value: dilated endoplasmic reticulum lumen

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the endoplasmic reticulum lumen is larger than normal.

label.value: dilated nuclear envelope lumen

value.value: An abnormal nuclear envelope morpbology in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the nuclear envelope lumen is larger than normal.

label.value: decreased RNA level during meiosis II

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell is lower than normal during the second meiotic nuclear division. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: heme absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount heme measured in a cell is too low to detect.

label.value: heme A absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount heme A measured in a cell is too low to detect.

label.value: heme O absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount heme O measured in a cell is too low to detect.

label.value: decreased level of heme O in cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of  heme O measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased ncRNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of non-coding RNA transcribed measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased mRNA splicing, meiotic genes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of mRNA splicing of meiosis specific genes is decreased during meiosis.

label.value: increased CUT RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of transcribed  cryptic unstable trancripts (CUTs) measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased non functional ncRNA level

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of non-functional non-coding RNA transcribed measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased rDNA intergenic repeat RNA level

definition.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA derived from rDNA intergenic repeat regions is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased nucleosome occupancy at centromeric heterochromatin

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is lower than normal in the pericentromeres. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: normal CUT RNA level

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of transcribed  cryptic unstable trancripts (CUTs) measured in a cell is  normal  (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).  Total CUT RNA or a CUT transcribed from a specific locus may be affected.

value.value: abolished protein localization to heterochromatin at  silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to heterochromatin at the silent mating-type cassette is abolished.

label.value: normal protein localization to centromeric heterochromatin

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to centromeric heterochromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type.

label.value: abnormal regulatory lncRNA 3'-end processing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulatory lncRNA 3' end processing is abnormal.

label.value: RNA absent from cell during cellular response to glucose starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell is too low to detect during a cellular response to glucose starvation. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

label.value: abnormal histone deacetylation at the silent mating-type locus during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone deacetylation is abnormal at the silent-mating type locus.

label.value: increased histone H3-S10 phosphorylation at the silent mating-type locus during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which phosphorylation of serine at position 10 of histone H3 is increased at the silent mating-type locus.

label.value: abolished histone H3-S10 phosphorylation at the silent mating-type locus during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone phosphorylation at the silent mating-type locus does not occur. All histone phosphorylation may be affected, or phosphorylation of specific sites on specific histones may be abolished.

label.value: normal histone H3-K56 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 56 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H4-K16 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 16 of histone H4 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased activation of S-phase DNA damage checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which the incidence of mitotic cell cycle arrest or delay due to regulation by the mitotic S-phase DNA damage checkpoint is greater than in wild type under any specified set of conditions.
